00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:27,000
There is this idea in education that
教育领域普遍认为

16
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,210
everyone has their own preferred way of learning,
每个人都有自己所倾向的学习方式

17
00:00:29,210 --> 00:00:31,160
their so-called learning style.
也就是通常所说的学习风格

18
00:00:31,160 --> 00:00:33,840
If information is presented in accordance with the learning style,
如果呈现信息的方式和学生的学习风格相匹配

19
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:36,090
well, then they'll learn better.
他们将能够学得更好

20
00:00:36,090 --> 00:00:38,950
Now, there are dozens of different learning style theories,
现在关于学习风格的理论有很多

21
00:00:38,950 --> 00:00:41,500
but the most common one identifies four main learning styles,
其中最著名的那个指出有四种主要的学习方式

22
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:47,132
visual, auditory, reading-writing, and kinesthetic or VARK for short.
视觉、听觉、读写以及动手，简称 VARK

23
00:00:47,132 --> 00:00:51,560
Visual learners learn best from images, demonstrations, and pictures.
视觉学习者从图像、图示等中学习效果最好

24
00:00:51,560 --> 00:00:54,110
- People may say things, but I can't really take it in.
有时别人通过说话的方式来教我 我吸收并不怎么样

25
00:00:54,110 --> 00:00:57,830
I just gotta see 'em act it out or write it or something.
我需要通过一些动作或者写出来这样来理解

26
00:00:57,830 --> 00:01:01,240
- Auditory learners learn best from listening to an explanation.
听觉学习者听别人讲解学习效果最佳

27
00:01:01,240 --> 00:01:04,410
- Like in school, I was always engaged in the lecture
- 在学校的时候我在课上很积极

28
00:01:04,410 --> 00:01:07,300
and that was usually good enough to pass a test.
也很有利于帮助我考试通过

29
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:10,100
- Reading-writing learners learn best from reading and writing.
- 读写学习者通过读和写来达到最佳的学习效果

30
00:01:10,100 --> 00:01:13,610
- Like I can get pretty much anything out of reading a textbook or something.
- 我读课本的时候能读出挺多东西的

31
00:01:13,610 --> 00:01:16,010
- And kinesthetic learners learn best by doing,
- 动手的学习者最有效的学习方式

32
00:01:16,010 --> 00:01:17,740
physically interacting with the world.
是真正的去接触东西，去实践

33
00:01:17,740 --> 00:01:18,573
- Hands-on.
- 上手去做

34
00:01:18,573 --> 00:01:20,500
You have to touch things, you have to play with things,
你需要去接触和把玩那些东西

35
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:24,550
you know, it's a contact sport. You have to do it yourself.
这个东西是要接触的 你必须得亲自去做才能学到 [REVIEW: "it"?]

36
00:01:24,550 --> 00:01:27,530
- I want to try something with you, a little experiment.
