00:01:35,493 --> 00:01:36,326
- Okay?
- Okay.
- 可以吗
- 可

42
00:01:36,326 --> 00:01:37,159
- Okay.
- 嗯

43
00:01:38,910 --> 00:01:43,510
- Now, learning styles make intuitive sense because we know everyone is different.
学习风格在直觉上挺合理的 我们都知道人和不一样

44
00:01:43,510 --> 00:01:45,960
Some people have better spacial reasoning.
有些人空间感知能力强

45
00:01:45,960 --> 00:01:48,580
Others have better listening comprehension.
有些人听力理解能力强

46
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:50,210
We know some people are better readers
有些人读文章强

47
00:01:50,210 --> 00:01:52,540
while others are good with their hands.
有些人动手能力强

48
00:01:52,540 --> 00:01:56,430
- It's sort of very much fits with a broad strain
这和一直流传下来的

49
00:01:56,430 --> 00:02:00,180
of thought in the recent Western tradition is,
近代的西方思想非常吻合

50
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:01,850
we're all unique, we're all different.
我们每个人都是独特、不同的

51
00:02:01,850 --> 00:02:04,157
And so you don't want to say, like, everybody learns the same way.
所以没必要每个人都用同一种方式来学习

52
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:09,190
That sort of conflicts with our feelings about what it means to be human.
学习方式完全一致与人类的意义相冲突

53
00:02:09,190 --> 00:02:10,500
- So doesn't it make sense that
那这样说的话

54
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:14,390
people should learn better in their own preferred learning style?
人们以自己的学习方式学习效果更好？

55
00:02:14,390 --> 00:02:16,720
Well, teachers certainly seem to think so.
啊，老师们当然这么想

56
00:02:16,720 --> 00:02:19,610
A survey of nearly 400 teachers from the UK and
英国和荷兰 400 名左右的教师里

57
00:02:19,410 --> 00:02:22,750
the Netherlands found that over 90% believed that
有超过 90% 的认为

58
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:27,340
individuals learn better when they receive information in their preferred learning style.
学生以他们的学习风格接收信息学得更快

59
00:02:27,340 --> 00:02:30,000
- Just like every professor has a different style of teaching,
- 教授有不同的教学方式

60
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,840
you have a different style of learning.
学生也有不同的学习方式

61
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:34,000
- But when his teacher starts using visuals,
- 当老师开始使用视觉方式教学时

62
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,910
Johnathan finds it easier to focus and understand the material
Johnathan 发现他理解课堂内容更快了 听课更专注了

63
00:02:36,910 --> 00:02:39,382
so he might be a visual learner.
因此他可能是个视觉学习者

64
00:02:39,382 --> 00:02:41,610
- Can you tell me what that means to you?
你能说一下作为一个视觉学习者

65
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:43,360
Like, what does it mean to be a visual learner?
这对你来说有什么样的意义吗

66
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:45,620
- To me it means that... for me, to learn something,
- 对我来说 这意味着我学东西的时候

67
00:02:45,620 --> 00:02:48,250
sometimes you need to draw it or I need to write it down
有时得要画出来或者写下来

68
00:02:48,250 --> 00:02:51,080
or I need to see a picture or a movie.
或者看图像、影片

69
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:55,000
- For example, science classes, I get bored easily just listening
例如科学课上听着听着我就睡着了

70
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:59,140
and I think it's more interesting for me to actually be able to do it.
能让我上手做我会更喜欢这个课

71
00:02:59,140 --> 00:03:00,750
- How do you know that you're a visual learner?
- 你咋知道你是视觉学习者的

72
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:02,253
- I don't, I just assumed.
- 不懂，我就觉得我是

73
00:03:03,380 --> 00:03:07,520
- To take advantage of learning styles then teachers need to do two things.
- 要把学生学习风格的优势运用起来 老师要做两件事

74
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:11,120
First, identify the learning style of each of their students.
首先他们要弄清楚他们各个学生的学习风格

75
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:15,550
And second, teach each student in accordance with their learning style.
然后根据各个学生的学习风格来教学

76
00:03:15,550 --> 00:03:17,200
On the VARK website it says,
在 VARK 的网站上

77
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:22,720
once you know about VARK, its power to explain things will be a revelation.
它说你一旦知道了这东西 你便知道了如何教别人的惊天秘密

78
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:25,310
But before you take an online learning styles quiz,
但是在你跑去测你的学习风格之前

79
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:29,060
